A Kabusa Grade I Area Court in Abuja has ordered that a 22-year-old student, Sadiq Adamu, be remanded in a Nasarawa correctional facility for allegedly stealing a car battery. Adamu was arraigned on Monday on a one-count charge. Prosecution Counsel, Mahmud Lawal, alleged that Adamu was arrested at Asokoro by a police patrol team, while in possession of the battery. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY Lawal told the court that the accused was caught with the battery, which he allegedly stole from an unknown person. He further told the court that during police investigation, it was discovered that Adamu had previously been convicted for a similar offence. He said the offence contravened the provisions of Sections 287 of the Penal Code. The Judge, Aliyu Kagarko, adjourned the case to Oct. 22 to hear the bail application. (NAN)  2 men bag 12 strokes of cane each for stealing car battery Farmer docked for allegedly raping 9-year-old girl Teenager allegedly kills friend over N3,000